{{Infobox journal | title = International Journal of Communication | cover = | editor = Larry Gross | discipline = [[Communication]], [[media studies]] | former_names = | abbreviation = Int. J. Commun. | publisher = [[USC Annenberg Press]] | country = United States | frequency = Continuously | history = 2007--present | openaccess = | license = [[Creative Commons license|CC BY-NC-ND]] | impact = | impact-year = | website = http://ijoc.org/ojs/index.php/ijoc | link1 = http://ijoc.org/ojs/index.php/ijoc/issue/archive | link1-name = Online archives | link2 = | link2-name = | JSTOR = | OCLC = 70824656 | LCCN = 2006213087 | CODEN = | ISSN = 1932-8036 | eISSN = }} The '''''International Journal of Communication''''' is an [[open access]] [[peer review|peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]] covering studies on [[communication]]. The [[editor-in-chief]] is Larry Gross ([[USC Annenberg School for Communication and Journalism]]) and it is published by the USC Annenberg Press (University of Southern California). The journal was established in 2007<ref>"[http://ulrichsweb.serialssolutions.com/title/1327328574016/637379 ''International Journal of Communication'']" (United States). ''[[Ulrich's Periodical Directory]]''. Retrieved on January 23, 2012.</ref> and is abstracted and indexed by the ''[[Social Sciences Citation Index]]'', ''[[Current Contents]]/Social & Behavioral Sciences'', and [[EBSCO Publishing|EBSCOhost]].
The journal publishes continuously, posting articles as soon as they are accepted.<ref>{{cite web|title=About the IJoC|url=http://ijoc.org/ojs/index.php/ijoc/about/aboutTheIJoC|accessdate=12 April 2012}}</ref>
