{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2013}} {{Infobox journal | title = Journal of Communication | cover = Journal of Communication.GIF | editor = Silvio Waisbord | discipline = [[Communication studies]] | former_names = | abbreviation = J. Commun. | publisher = [[Oxford University Press]] | country = | frequency = Bimonthly | history = 1951-present | openaccess = | license = | impact = 3.914 | impact-year = 2016 | website = https://academic.oup.com/joc | link3 = http://www.icahdq.org/pubs/jnlofcomm.asp | link3-name = Journal page at association's website | JSTOR = | OCLC = 01754508 | LCCN = 56046080 | CODEN = | ISSN = 0021-9916 | eISSN = 1460-2466 }} The '''''Journal of Communication''''' is a bimonthly [[Peer review|peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]] that publishes articles and book reviews on a broad range of issues in [[communication theory]] and research. It was established in 1951 and the current [[editor-in-chief]] is Silvio Waisbord ([[George Washington University]]). According to the ''[[Journal Citation Reports]]'', its 2014 [[impact factor]] is 3.16. The ''Journal of Communication'' is ranked first out of 76 journals in the category "Communication".<ref name=WoS>{{cite book |year=2014 |chapter=Journals Ranked by Impact: Communication |title=2013 [[Journal Citation Reports]] |publisher=[[Thomson Reuters]] |edition=Social Sciences |accessdate=2012-08-02 |series=[[Web of Science]] |postscript=.}}</ref> It is published by [[Oxford University Press]] on behalf of the [[International Communication Association]].
